Fatima Yasmin Kure, the first daughter of late Niger state Governor, Engineer Abdulkadir Kure, is dead. It was gathered that she died suddenly in Abuja. Niger State Governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani-Bello, has commiserated with the family over the incident. The Governor expressed shock over the demise of Yasmin, a mother of one in Abuja. He asked Allah to grant the soul of the deceased eternal rest, reward her with Jannatul Firdausi and grant Senator Zainab Kure and entire the family the fortitude to bear the loss. The Governor sent a strong delegation to attend the burial rites of late Fatima Yasmin Abdulkadir Kure at the National Mosque, Abuja.  